<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="4.0">The private school, Wilcox Academy, is what researchers call a “<a href="https://etd.auburn.edu/bitstream/handle/10415/8176/AmberlySheffield%20Thesis.pdf?sequence=2">segregation academy</a>” due to the historic whiteness of its student body and the timing of its opening. It’s down to 200 students across 12 grades. Housed in a single-story building with beige siding and brown brick veneer, the school offers chapel and core academic classes but not music, theater or band programs.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="5"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size10 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


