        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/wilcox-county-alabama-segregation-academies">
                                    How Residents in a Rural Alabama County Are Confronting the Lasting Harm of Segregation Academies
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            In Wilcox County, Alabama, many people say they want to bridge racial divides created by their segregated schools. But they must face a long and painful history.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/jennifer-berry-hawes">Jennifer Berry Hawes</a>, photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-24EDT06:00">May 24, 6 a.m. EDT</time>
